The paper focuses on analyzing social networks using machine learning techniques, which falls under the scope of social and information networks (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of clustering algorithms and clique detection also suggests that the paper could be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.SD). The potential applications for advertising and recommendation systems suggest that the paper could also be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the focus on social networks and community detection suggests that the paper could be categorized under social and economic networks (cs.SOC).
